binary tree types:

FULL BINARY TREE - every node has either 0 or 2 children.
COMPLETE BINARY TREE - all levels are completely filled except last level & the last level shd have everything as left as pssble.
PERFECT BINARY TREE - all leaf nodes at same level
BALANCED BINARY TREE - height of tree is at max log(n) where n is number of nodes
DEGENERATE TREE - every node has single child. eg: 0
                                                  /
                                                0
                                              /
                                             0
